1) Install Pinax and activate your virtualenv
    http://pinaxproject.com/docs/dev/install.html#install-released-tarball-instructions

2) Checkout django-newsroom pinax branch inside the virtualenv
    svn co https://django-newsroom.googlecode.com/svn/branches/pinax --username

3) Install DN requirements 
    pip install -r requirements/external_apps.txt

4) Install caveats by hand (django-countries) according to
    http://code.google.com/p/django-newsroom/source/browse/trunk/docs/install.txt#73

5) Make sure you have django trunk
    pip install -e svn+http://code.djangoproject.com/svn/django/trunk#egg=django-trunk

6) Create the database from your postgis template
   createdb -T template_postgis -O <db user> -h localhost -p5432 -U <db user> -W <db name>

7) Create the tables in your db
    ./manage.py syncdb

8) Add the so-called “Google” projection to your spatial database’s spatial_ref_sys table 
    from django.contrib.gis.utils import add_postgis_srs
    add_postgis_srs(900913)

9) Use this shell script or run the commands to get the GeoIP data sets:  http://bazaar.launchpad.net/%7Epopulous/django-geotagging/geotags/annotate/head%3A/geotagging_demo_project/geoip_datasets/get_geoip_datasets.sh

10) Run the test suite to make sure that everything is properly setup
    ./manage.py test stories videos photos page_layouts
